                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons">Jacob the Recluse
                        fled for the desert of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/715">Egypt</placeName> during the persecution of the emperor Julian. He then
                        headed to East to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1452">Mesopotamia</placeName> with companions. They lived in a tower.
                        Eventually he built a monastery at <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2">Salah</placeName> in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/221">Ṭur ʿAbdin</placeName>.</note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="discursive" source="#bib1299-3">Nau offers a summary
                        of his story.</note>
